Currently [you need to create a VSCode extension](https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/customization/colorizer#_common-questions) to map extensions that are not listed under a language to an existing language. In most cases I want to map a certain extension to a certain language and it shouldn't be this hard. A simple JavaScript object in the editor settings should be enough.

Something like this:

``` json
{
  "fileExtensionMapping": {
    "md": ["markdown", "mkdown"],
    "ng": "html"
  }
}
```
